A Chinese-made luxury "RORO" (roll-on/roll-off) passenger ship was delivered to the buyer on Tuesday in Guangzhou City, south China's Guangdong Province. With a maximum speed of 23 knots, the ship named "Xiang Long Dao" is the fastest of its kind in the country. Measuring 208 meters long and 28.6 meters wide, it can carry as many as 1,375 passengers and more than 500 vehicles. Built by the Guangzhou Shipyard International Company, the new ship is also the country's most intelligent and environmentally friendly RORO passenger ship.